						               													<description>The series Dominoplay, created by Flavio Fogarolo, offers fun, didactic games which are variations on the classic game of dominoes, excellent for supporting learning and automatisms, especially but not only in calculations.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dominoplay enables children to have instant control of the right matches: in fact, each element has a multi-coloured edge, a sort of colour barcode, which identifies the quantity represented, despite being presented under a different guise. If children try to pair up dominoes with different values they&amp;rsquo;ll realise immediately.&amp;#10;Thanks to the effective checking system, they can play fractions and decimals dominoes independently, even with the tables they don&amp;rsquo;t know perfectly, without needing the constant supervision of an adult.&amp;#10;Each game is divided into three levels of increasing difficulty and you can choose to play with only the dominoes belonging to the first level, only those from the second or the third level, those form the second and the third level together or the whole pack.&amp;#10;Dominoplay is a fun didactic tool and is ideal for encouraging inclusion: by carefully choosing the groups of dominoes all children can learn and have fun!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dominoplay &amp;ndash; Fractions and decimals provides exercises on fractions and decimals, using pictures as well.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
